Paper: hep-th/9511051

Date: 1995-11-07

Title: Threshhold Singularities and the Magnetic Mass in Hot QCD

Authors: R. Jackiw (MIT) and So-Young Pi (Boston University)

Comments: 10 pages in REVTEX, with 3 PostScript figures inside

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B368 (1996) 131-136

We discuss the recently devised one-loop gap equation for the magnetic massof hot QCD. An alternative, and one would hope equivalent, gap equation ispresented, which however shows no mass generation at the one-loop level.